Mafdet views the five-city realm as a conversion system: inland value must reach the sea and satisfy maritime standards.
Position at Saltglass Reach's terminus: every inland claim tested against maritime legitimacy before ocean transfer.
Document standards conflict: Midgaard charters may fail Mafdet's Quarantine Ledger; Claw Mark Registry may fail Kowloon's Black Ledger.
Shoreward Conversion is a daily negotiation between two legal systems that have never fully reconciled.
Realm works when all city standards are mutually legible; fails when cities speak only to their own registries.
Strandline Compact harbor-first principle: every political decision tested against throughput.
City relations: aligned with Kowloon on throughput, Midgaard on authentication, and Kiess on caravan route law.
Shrine of the First Claw oath tradition: Mafdet is where inland promises meet the sea's accountability standards.
Mafdet's assessment: the realm is a chain. Mafdet is its last conversion point.
